  "doc_id": "30775",
  "text": "In our study, antidepressant treatment was one of the exclusion criteria. Although antipsychotic genesis of depressive syndrome in schizophrenia is often mentioned, Krakowski et al [CITATION_1] found that antipsychotics might have two-sided effect on depressive symptoms, while Siris et al [CITATION_2] did not find any difference in the prevalence of depression in schizophrenia between patients who were and those who were not treated with antipsychotics. A study with drug-untreated patients might show different results.",
